Package: squelchbreak
Version: 2026.06.21.01-1
Section: hamradio
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Kari Karvonen <oh1kk@toimii.fi>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-4.0, gir1.2-adw-1, python3-pyaudio
Recommends: portaudio19-dev
Homepage: https://github.com/OH1KK/squelchbreak
Description: VOX-triggered audio recorder for amateur radio / scanner use
 Squelchbreak listens to an audio input device and automatically
 records whenever the signal "breaks squelch" (exceeds a configurable
 threshold), stopping again after a period of silence. Designed for
 amateur radio and scanner monitoring, with a native GNOME (GTK4 +
 libadwaita) interface.
 .
 Features include a VU meter with a visible threshold marker, manual
 record mode, per-recording JSON metadata sidecars (optionally
 populated by a user-supplied script querying a radio over serial/
 rigctl), automatic recovery from a stuck/frozen audio device, and
 support for running multiple independent instances at once (one per
 sound card/radio) via per-instance config files.
